textAfterTable: 14 canciones Reseña de álbum This fine overview of Mystikal's years on Jive has the rapper's six-year jail sentence hanging over it, giving his hedonistic party jams a totally different context. The new "P***y Pop" single is slick, there's one other unreleased track, and none of the latter-day hits escapes the collection. Biografía Nacido(a): 22 de septiembre de 1970 en New Orleans, LA Género: Hip-Hop/Rap Años de actividad: '90s, '00s, '10s Once one of the leading rappers on Master P's No Limit record label, Mystikal quickly evolved beyond the label's clichéd thug trappings and found himself one of the Dirty South's most recognized rappers, alongside the likes of Juvenile and Ludacris. Like No Limit itself, Mystikal is a New Orleans native. He released an eponymous debut on the independent label Big Boy in June 1995.
